Generate Php code that creates an abstract base class without boilerplate using Php’s built-in abstract classes and methods, like this:

```php
abstract class MyClass {
   abstract public function my_method(): void;
}
```

This will create a class `MyClass` that has an abstract method `my_method`, which can be implemented by any subclass of `MyClass`. Php’s class system handles the default constructor automatically if you don’t define one, so you don’t need to write it yourself.
